Audiovisual productions "from the periphery" have nowadays more space for display, mainly in festivals such as Cine Cufa and Peripheral Visions. Considering the existence of a speech guided by the right to self-representation, which organize and gives support to the so-called "cinema of the periphery", this article presents some thoughts on how this specific audiovisual production articulates social representations around subjects and territories peripherals and is used as an instrument of struggle for recognition.